getTokenContract(string).details: Get Token's contract address deployed by tokenize function'.

params.tokenSymbol: symbol of the token whose contract address to return.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

issueTokens(string,address).details: Issue Tokens to given asset owner'.

params.owner: Account of owner to whom tokens to be issued. Requirements:     * - only contract owner can perform this action

issueTokens(string,address).return: true in case tokens issued to owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setDocument(bytes32,string,bytes32,strin.details: Set document to given token's contract'.

params.name: document name.
params.tokenSymbol: symbol of the token whose document to be set. Requirements:     * - only contract owner can perform this action

setDocument(bytes32,string,bytes32,strin.return: true in case document is store in asset's contract.

tokenize(string,string,uint256).details: Tokenize the asset according to provided details'.

params.name: Asset's tokens name.
params.supply: Tokens total supply which need to be created. Requirements:     * - only contract owner can perform this action

tokenize(string,string,uint256).return: true in case asset is tokenized.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(address,address,uint256,string).details: withdraw tokens from specific account to provided account.

params.from: The address from whom tokens to be withdrawn.
params.value: The value of tokens to be withdrawn. Requirements:     * - only contract owner can perform this action

withdraw(address,address,uint256,string).return: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.
